2008-05-27 09:18:01 (2195 days ago)
<div id='contact-1'>x (1)</div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
The posted property starts up at the curve in Aska Road and extends down to a drainage pipe down by<br/>
the rocks. The landowner actually painted an orange line on the rocks designating her property<br/>
line. Down stream from this line and the drainage pipe there is room to park cars and sit on the<br/>
rocks. There is about 200 feet of space downstream from the line where it is business as usual. On<br/>
5/26/08 I witnessed landowner tell folks sitting on her side of the rocks to move over to the other<br/>
side of her line. Tubing and kayaking outfitters still use this part of the pull-off to service<br/>
their clients. I rented a kayak from Jon Ron (about 100 yards upstream on Aska Rd) and he said he<br/>
leases the lower portion of the pull off and it's cool to park there. </div>
